# Sponsor Hanakai. Help us build a diverse future for Ruby.

~~~
For more than a decade, Hanami, Dry and Rom have offered Ruby developers something different: tools built around clarity, flexibility, and a genuine belief that there's more than one good way to build an app. This year we've brought all three together under Hanakai, a unified project with a shared community and future. We've delivered on this. Now comes the part where we make it last.

Sustaining Hanakai means steady, ongoing work: releasing gems, improving your developer experience, and growing our community. This needs me to show up consistently, over the long run. And beyond that, we want more of our maintainers to get the recognition and compensation they deserve.

Ruby is a better place when there are real alternatives to reach for. If you believe this — or if Dry, Rom or Hanami are already doing important work somewhere in your stack — sponsorship is how you grow Hanakai and Ruby’s diversity along with it.

— Tim Riley
  Hanakai project lead
~~~

## How we use your money

Every dollar goes directly to sustaining Hanakai:

* **Up to $30k/year** funds one day a week of Tim’s time, as lead maintainer.
* **$30-40k/year** builds a reserve for community and promotional activities.
* **Beyond $40k/year** pays additional Hanakai maintainers for their ongoing work.

We are currently supported at $26k/year.

## How to sponsor us

You can sponsor us via [Open Collective](https://opencollective.com/hanami) or [GitHub Sponsors](https://github.com/sponsors/hanami), as a business or an individual.

## Become a business sponsor

As a Hanakai business sponsor, you'll receive several benefits:

- Private chat with Hanakai maintainers
- Priority attention on issues or requests
- Your logo and link on our website
- Shoutouts on social media and in release announcements

Most important of all, you’ll be creating a healthy and diverse future for Ruby.

